===================NGNIX INSTALL / CONFIG / DEPLOY=========

-- Install EPEL Repository (if needed): Nginx is often available in the EPEL (Extra Packages for Enterprise Linux) repository.

sudo yum install epel-release

sudo yum install nginx

Start the service  ; 
Enable the service ;If you want a start automatically after boot

/usr/share/ngnix/html - Website file


================SETUP SSL FOR NGNIX==================

 ssl_certificate "/etc/pki/nginx/server.crt";
        ssl_certificate_key "/etc/pki/nginx/private/server.key";
        ssl_session_cache shared:SSL:1m;
		
--->> THIS IS my location in the nginx.conf file
-- Place the .crt and .key files in the respective locations
-- Restart the service  


Done !!!
